title: A spontaneous eulogy for Lee Konitz

http_headers.User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/73.0.3673.2 Safari/537.36

description:
I was asked by the Jazz Gallery in New York to contribute a short video about master improviser saxophonist Lee Konitz, who died on April 15th at age 92, for an online memorial. I sat down in front of the camera and spoke spontaneously, the way I think Lee would have done it. 

I devoted my April 20th livestream to him: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sjcye4McdLU
Here's a beautiful documentary about a duo tour we did together: https://www.dailymotion.com/video/x2ytdgp
fulltitle: A spontaneous eulogy for Lee Konitz
